#: materiel-identity.rst:63
msgid "Entering ``materiel`` defines the claim and defines the relevant fields to be used in further data entry about a :ref:`materiel`. For quality assurance purposes, entering ``materiel`` should create an error if there is any entry for fields tied to other claim types, such as :ref:`equipment` or :ref:`component`."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:66
msgid "status:meta"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:72
msgid "A field that classifies the data in the claim."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:87
msgid "``:claim/statuses``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:92
msgid "``accepted``, ``conflict``, ``work_needed``, ``issue``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:97
msgid "Claims are marked ``accepted`` when all of the data can be entered in accordance with the guidance of this handbook. The ``conflict`` flag is used whenever a claim conflicts with another claim (or claims) and a review of citations show it to be the incorrect or false claim (see :ref:`Citations with both Accepted and Conflicted Information` for guidance when one claim from a citation contains both ``accepted`` and ``conflict`` information). A :ref:`public_notes:meta <materiel-public-notes>` should always accompany any ``conflict`` claim."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:99
msgid "If the data itself cannot be brought into the SFM standard the flag ``issue`` should be used. Finally, if the current citations cannot establish whether a claim should be flagged as ``accepted`` or ``conflict`` then the flag ``work_needed`` should be used as additional research is needed."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:102
msgid "researcher:meta"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:108
msgid "Field for initials or other identifier of researcher who last entered data for the claim."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:123
msgid "``:meta/researchers``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:128
msgid "``TW``, ``Jane_Doe``, ``G1``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:133
msgid "Every researcher should use this field to mark the claims that they have entered. Anytime a researcher modifies any data for an existing claim they should update this field so that any questions can be directed to the right person and the flow of work can be better tracked."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:136
msgid "internal_comments:meta"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:142
msgid "A field for temporary comments or notes for the researcher or research team working on the claim."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:152 materiel-identity.rst:255 materiel-identity.rst:291 materiel-identity.rst:359 materiel-identity.rst:393 materiel-identity.rst:427 materiel-identity.rst:461 materiel-identity.rst:495 materiel-identity.rst:529 materiel-identity.rst:563 materiel-identity.rst:597 materiel-identity.rst:631 materiel-identity.rst:665 materiel-identity.rst:699 materiel-identity.rst:735
msgid "This attribute is optional."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:157
msgid "``:meta/internal-comments``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:162
msgid "``Come back to this to determine date for claim``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:167
msgid "Researchers may use this field to make temporary notes or leave temporary comments intended for others in the research team about a claim. These should eventually be addressed and the field cleared by the researcher or research team. If the claim needs an explanatory note or comment to be better understood, then that should be entered in the :ref:`public_notes:meta <materiel-public-notes>` field."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:170
msgid "citation:refs:claim"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:176
msgid "Field unique 32 character code assigned to citation(s) evidencing the claim."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:181 materiel-identity.rst:216
msgid "String in UUID format"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:191
msgid "``:claim/citation:refs``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:196
msgid "``69dba35b-2b70-47cf-bfda-f80225f652c6``, ``4e99308c-f9c0-49e8-b97b-14c1e7bcb99d;bedf57b2-c20b-41e3-9dcf-b7b065eaa3b7``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:201
msgid "Every claim must have at least one citation to evidence the data in the claim. When two or more citations are needed to evidence a claim then a corresponding explanatory note should be entered in the :ref:`public_notes:meta <materiel-public-notes>` field. This field is for the Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for each citation, found in the :ref:`source:access_point_id:admin` field in the Sources sheet. When multiple citations are needed every UUID should be semi-colon separated."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:205
msgid "about_entity:ref:claim"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:211
msgid "A unique 32 character code assigned to each entity in the dataset."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:226
msgid "``:claim/about-entity:ref``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:231
msgid "``521ebf18-f161-4ac9-8c72-5a246efa0458``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:236
msgid "Every entity has a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) to distinguish it from any other entity. For :ref:`materiel` this UUID distinguishes them from any other :ref:`materiel` in the dataset. This UUID is used in other fields to tie :ref:`materiel` to a specific :ref:`unit` as :ref:`equipment` or as a :ref:`component` (or part) of other :ref:`materiel`."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:239
msgid "about_entity:name:qa"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:245
msgid "Field that provides human readable name for entity."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:260
msgid "n/a"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:265
msgid "``MiG-21UM``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:270
msgid "This field provides a human readable counterpart to the :ref:`about_entity:ref:claim <materiel-about-entity>` which combines the various elements of the claim into a single text field. This field can be manually added by a researcher or automatically populated by the system after import. For :ref:`materiel` best practice is to use the :ref:`name:annotation <materiel-name-annotation>` in this field."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:275
msgid "name:annotation"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:281
msgid "Fullest name of the materiel as evidenced by citations."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:286 materiel-identity.rst:320 materiel-identity.rst:660 materiel-identity.rst:694 materiel-identity.rst:730
msgid "String"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:296
msgid "``:annotation/name``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:301
msgid "``MiG-21UM``, ``Universal Water Activated Release System``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:306
msgid "As with all annotation fields, this field is the singular display name for the entity. For :ref:`materiel` this field is only used if the citation evidences the fullest name of the :ref:`materiel` which is defined as the name with the highest number of characters."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:309
msgid "materiel:names:assertion"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:315
msgid "Any name given for the materiel from citation."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:330 materiel-identity.rst:364 materiel-identity.rst:398 materiel-identity.rst:432
msgid "n/a - proposed field"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:335
msgid "``MiG``, ``UWARS``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:340
msgid "Any name for :ref:`materiel` used in the citation should be entered in this field. While the :ref:`name:annotation <materiel-name-annotation>` field is only used for a single, most complex value, this field is used for any name a citation uses for :ref:`materiel`. Thus, this field serves to capture \"aliases\" of the :ref:`materiel`, which also includes any typos or misspellings that may exist in the citation."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:343
msgid "materiel:classifications:assertion"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:349
msgid "A general descriptor for the materiel."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-identity.rst:354 materiel-identity.rst:388 materiel-identity.rst:422 materiel-identity.rst:764
